## Budget Considerations When Choosing a Family Pet

[Owning a pet](/adoption) is not just an emotional commitment—it’s a financial one too. From food and bedding to vet visits and grooming, understanding costs helps you plan better and avoid surprises later.

| Expense             | Dogs            | Cats            | Small Pets     |
| :------------------ | :-------------- | :-------------- | :------------- |
| **Food & Treats**   | $800–$1200/year | $600–$1000/year | $200–$500/year |
| **Vet Care**        | $400–$1000/year | $300–$800/year  | $100–$200/year |
| **Grooming**        | $200–$800/year  | $100–$300/year  | Minimal        |
| **Supplies & Toys** | $150–$300/year  | $100–$200/year  | $50–$150/year  |

**Pro Tip from Pets Playground:** Always factor in pet insurance and emergency expenses—especially for dogs and cats. It’s better to be prepared than stressed when your furry friend needs help.

